<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96880271225189></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96880271225189><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96880271225189>RE: The next big secret</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=96880271225189#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 12th 7:51 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually there are a couple of errors here.&nbsp;&nbsp;For one group experience is not split evenly.  Instead the amount of exp needed to level for each group member is added together to form a total exp needed value.  Then the exp needed to level for each member is divided by the total exp needed value to form a percentage which is multiplied by the mob experience and the result is given to the group member.  In short the exp calc for grouping is: ((amount needed by player)/(sum of amount needed by group))*(mob exp).  <br><br>On death, the amount of exp you lose is based on a percentage of the amount of experience a human warrior needed to travel through the last level.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
